“Look at that chap now,” philosophically drawled Stubb, who, with his 
unlighted short pipe, mechanically retained between his teeth, at a short 
distance, followed after—“He’s got fits, that Flask has. Fits? yes, give 
him fits—that’s the very word—pitch fits into ’em. Merrily, merrily, 
hearts-alive. Pudding for supper, you know;—merry’s the word. Pull, 
